# Internal-only / working-memory files — not published to the public repo.
# These document private project state (session handoffs, personal task
# lists, etc.) and are excluded by intent.
#
# `/CLAUDE.md` is intentionally NOT listed here — the public, cleaned-up
# project agent instructions are tracked. Personal cross-project memory
# stays in `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`.
/HANDOFF.md
# Exclude docs/ contents by default, then whitelist the public surface.
# Anything not whitelisted stays gitignored (research/, sources/,
# superpowers/, source-materials/, …) as private exploration scratch.
# (Git cannot re-include files under a fully-excluded parent directory,
#  so we exclude contents with /docs/* instead of the dir itself.)
/docs/*
!/docs/adr/
# .private/ is an independent nested git repository for private session state
# (STATE.md, TODO.md, etc.). The outer repo MUST NOT track it at all.
/.private/

# Environment / Secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.production
# (commit .env.example as template)
!.env.example
*.pem
*-key.pem
*.key
!*.public.key
secrets/

# Claude Code config — local/per-machine settings stay private, but the
# shared team settings file is tracked so repo conventions (e.g. AI-attribution
# trailer policy) apply to every contributor. Git cannot re-include a file under
# a fully-excluded dir, so exclude contents with /* then whitelist the one file.
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json

